---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Will Harvey | Leadership Growth Consulting"
  description="I work inside businesses alongside their owners, building the systems, teams, and structure that let them step back without things falling apart."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-white pt-28 pb-16 lg:pt-36 lg:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-brand uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-semibold mb-6">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-zinc-900 leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        Will Harvey
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-zinc-500 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
        I work inside businesses alongside their owners. Building the systems, the teams, and
        the structure that lets them step back without things falling apart.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PHOTO + INTRO -->
  <section class="bg-white pb-20 lg:pb-28">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <img
            src="/images/will.jpg"
            alt="Will Harvey"
            width="600"
            height="750"
            loading="lazy"
            class="w-full aspect-[4/5] object-cover object-top grayscale"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-10 pt-4">
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-zinc-900 mb-5">How I got here</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                I have spent over eight years working directly with business owners, and longer
                than that in and around sales leadership, team development, and operational
                problem-solving. I have built sales teams from scratch, led them, fixed what
                was not working, and developed the people doing the work.
              </p>
              <p>
                Along the way I have worked with senior leaders across organisations like KPMG,
                DocuSign, HSBC Asset Management, Bloom and Wild, MyTutor, and Vizolution, alongside
                smaller owner-led businesses like Taxi for Email, Action Rocket, Guest 365, MJS Tax,
                and Adare Pharma Solutions. Not all of that was AI and efficiency work. Much of it
                was leadership development, sales enablement, and helping good people do better work.
              </p>
              <p>
                But the pattern was always the same: the owner was stuck in the middle of everything,
                and the business could not grow past what they could personally manage. Eventually I
                stopped coaching from the sidelines and started getting into the business itself. Building
                the systems, hiring the right people, setting up the processes, and doing whatever it
                takes to make the thing actually work without everything running through one person.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-zinc-900 mb-5">How I work</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                I do not do the flying visit. I get into the business, understand what is actually
                going on, and work alongside you over months. Not a one-off strategy day and a
                slide deck.
              </p>
              <p>
                Most engagements start with a discovery conversation, then a proper strategy
                session. From there we work together weekly, building what needs to be built and
                fixing what is getting in the way.
              </p>
              <p>
                It is part coaching, part consulting, part just getting things done together.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT I BRING -->
  <section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-zinc-900 mb-6">What I bring to the table</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
          <p>
            I work with business owners, typically running teams of 5 to 20 people, who are profitable
            but stretched. The business works. It works because they make it work. And that is exactly
            the problem.
          </p>
          <p>
            I have been alongside enough owners to know what the common patterns are and what
            actually fixes them. Most of the time, it is not one big thing. It is a combination of
            the right people, the right systems, and someone willing to get in and do the work with
            you until it sticks.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-10">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-zinc-600">
            <svg class="text-brand mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 8L6.5 11.5L13 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
            Build the sales structure so the business is not dependent on the owner to close every deal
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-zinc-600">
            <svg class="text-brand mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 8L6.5 11.5L13 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
            Hire the right people and set them up to actually do the job
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-zinc-600">
            <svg class="text-brand mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 8L6.5 11.5L13 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
            Put the right systems in place so things genuinely get easier, not more complicated
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-zinc-600">
            <svg class="text-brand mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none">
              <path d="M3 8L6.5 11.5L13 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
            Get clear on where the owner's attention should actually go
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
          The result, in most cases, is a business owner who has more space in their week. To think
          strategically. To actually be present at home. To do the things outside of work that
          matter to them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS -->
  <section class="bg-white py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 text-center">
        <div>
          <p class="font-serif text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-zinc-900 mb-2">8+</p>
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Years working directly with business owners</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-serif text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-zinc-900 mb-2">7 figures</p>
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Supported owners to exit at multiple 7-figure valuations</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-serif text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-zinc-900 mb-2">1,000s</p>
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Hours saved through better systems and processes</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PERSONAL -->
  <section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-zinc-900 mb-6">Outside of work</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          <p>
            I am based in Surrey. My honest ambition outside the work is pretty simple: quality time
            with family, a business that genuinely helps people, and more rounds of golf with friends
            and family.
          </p>
          <p>
            If I can find a way to pull all three together properly (still working on it), that is
            the version of life I am building towards. It is the same thing most of the owners I work
            with are after: a business that works, and a life around it that is actually worth living.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PULL QUOTE -->
  <section class="bg-brand py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <blockquote class="font-serif text-2xl lg:text-3xl text-white italic leading-relaxed">
        "The goal is not to work less. It is to work on the right things, and have a life around it."
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-zinc-900 mb-4">Want to talk?</h2>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 text-lg mb-8">If any of this resonates, the best next step is a conversation.</p>
      <a
        href="https://calendly.com/will-leadershipgrowthconsulting/30min"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-block bg-brand text-white px-8 py-4 font-medium hover:bg-brand-hover transition-colors"
      >
        Book a discovery call
      </a>
      <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm mt-4">No pitch. Just a straight conversation about where you are.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
